cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with deep neural networks and their application in computer vision, specifically in the domain adaptation problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning algorithms, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of hashing for storage and retrieval efficiency suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with classification and retrieval of data, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of deep neural networks for feature learning suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category.
